2026-04-13 | Next Smallest Palindrome Greater Than Given Number

	Question
Return next smallest palindrome as array.

	Approach
1.	Mirror left half to right:
		make number palindrome  

2.	Check:
		if mirrored number > original → done  

3.	If NOT:
		need to increment middle and propagate carry  

4.	Steps:
	- Start from middle  
	- Add 1 and handle carry  
	- Mirror again  

5.	Edge case:
		all digits are 9 → answer is:
			1 0 0 ... 0 1  

	Time Complexity
	O(n)

	Space Complexity
	O(1)

	Solution

class Solution {
public:
    vector<int> generateNextPalindrome(vector<int>& num) {

        int n = num.size();

        // check all 9s
        bool all9 = true;
        for(int x : num){
            if(x != 9){
                all9 = false;
                break;
            }
        }

        if(all9){
            vector<int> res(n+1, 0);
            res[0] = res[n] = 1;
            return res;
        }

        vector<int> res = num;

        // mirror left to right
        for(int i = 0; i < n/2; i++){
            res[n-1-i] = res[i];
        }

        // check if already greater
        if(res > num) return res;

        // increment middle
        int carry = 1;
        int mid = n/2;

        if(n % 2 == 1){
            res[mid] += carry;
            carry = res[mid] / 10;
            res[mid] %= 10;
            mid--;
        } else {
            mid = n/2 - 1;
        }

        while(mid >= 0 && carry){
            res[mid] += carry;
            carry = res[mid] / 10;
            res[mid] %= 10;
            mid--;
        }

        // mirror again
        for(int i = 0; i < n/2; i++){
            res[n-1-i] = res[i];
        }

        return res;
    }
};

	Key Insight
Two main steps:
1.	Try simple mirroring  
2.	If not enough → increment middle and mirror again  

This guarantees the **smallest palindrome strictly greater** than input in O(n).
